The arrest comes hours after Mr Museveni warned Wine and members of his National Unity Platform (NUP) against causing chaos ahead of his swearing ceremony in May. Ugandan politician Robert Kyagulanyi alias Bobi Wine has been arrested while leading a peaceful demonstration demanding the release of hundreds of his supporters who went missing after they were arrested during and after the January 14 election. 

The runner-up in the presidential poll, which saw Yoweri Museveni re-elected, was on Monday intercepted by police at City Square in Kampala. 



